        <untitled-ontology-3:descricao>&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Caso de teste do caso de uso&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Definir entradas de teste e resultados esperados para ajudar a avaliar se um sistema funciona corretamente.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Pode haver um ou mais Casos de Teste para verificar cada Fatia de Caso de Uso.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Fornecer os blocos de constru&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o para projetar e implementar testes.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Fornecer um mecanismo para completar e verificar os requisitos.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Permitir que os testes sejam especificados antes do in&amp;iacute;cio da implementa&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 1em; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Fornecer uma maneira de avaliar a qualidade do sistema&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Apresenta&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Os melhores casos de teste descrevem cen&amp;aacute;rios de teste, onde um cen&amp;aacute;rio &amp;eacute; um thread completo de execu&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o no sistema.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: start;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Casos de teste para testes de casos de uso&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Os casos de teste s&amp;atilde;o um complemento importante, mas muitas vezes negligenciado, de um caso de uso. Os casos de teste fornecem a verdadeira defini&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o do que o sistema deve fazer para dar suporte a um caso de uso. Os casos de teste s&amp;atilde;o particularmente importantes quando come&amp;ccedil;amos a dividir os casos de uso, pois fornecem aos desenvolvedores uma defini&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o clara do que significa implementar com sucesso uma fatia de casos de uso.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;text-align: justify; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Os casos de teste podem ser usados com muitas formas de pr&amp;aacute;tica de requisitos, incluindo casos de uso, hist&amp;oacute;rias de usu&amp;aacute;rios e requisitos declarativos. Em todos os casos, o testador deve receber uma fatia dos requisitos a serem testados, com in&amp;iacute;cio e fim claros, a partir dos quais eles possam derivar um cen&amp;aacute;rio de teste execut&amp;aacute;vel.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Informa&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es adicionais&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: start;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size: 1.75em;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Conte&amp;uacute;do essencial&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;1..N Pr&amp;eacute;-condi&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es: Pr&amp;eacute;-condi&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es que especificam o estado do sistema antes do teste.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;1..N Entrada: As mensagens e dados a serem recebidos nas entradas espec&amp;iacute;ficas do cen&amp;aacute;rio.&amp;nbsp;Para os n&amp;iacute;veis iniciais de detalhe, estes podem ser apenas os dados iniciais necess&amp;aacute;rios para iniciar o cen&amp;aacute;rio.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;1 Cen&amp;aacute;rio de Teste: O cen&amp;aacute;rio que o caso de teste ir&amp;aacute; exercer.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;1..N Observa&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es (com resultados esperados): As observa&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es a serem feitas &amp;agrave; medida que o caso de teste &amp;eacute; executado incluindo o resultado esperado. Isto inclui a descri&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o de quaisquer p&amp;oacute;s-condi&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es desejadas do sistema e como os resultados esperados ser&amp;atilde;o verificados.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: start;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size: 1.75em;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Conte&amp;uacute;do adicional&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-align: start; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;N / D&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</untitled-ontology-3:descricao>
        <untitled-ontology-3:nome>&lt;p&gt;Caso de teste do caso de uso&lt;/p&gt;</untitled-ontology-3:nome>
        <untitled-ontology-3:referenciaRE>&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Refer&amp;ecirc;ncias&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: start;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;sup&gt;&lt;sup style=&quot;font-size: smaller;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt; What is a Good Test Case?, by Cem Kaner, Star East, 2003.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: start;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;sup&gt;&lt;sup style=&quot;font-size: smaller;&quot;&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; The Unified Software Development Process, by Ivar Jacobson, Grady Booch and James Rumbaugh, Addison Wesley Longman, chapter 11.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: start;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;sup&gt;&lt;sup style=&quot;font-size: smaller;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; The Art of Software Testing, by Glenford J. Myers, John Wiley and Sons, Inc., New York, 1979.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: start;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;sup&gt;&lt;sup style=&quot;font-size: smaller;&quot;&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; &lt;u&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.extremeprogramming.org/rules/functionaltests.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(75, 110, 198);&quot;&gt;www.extremeprogramming.org/rules/functionaltests.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: start;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;sup&gt;&lt;sup style=&quot;font-size: smaller;&quot;&gt;5&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.extremeprogramming.org/rules/testfirst.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(75, 110, 198);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;www.extremeprogramming.org/rules/testfirst.html&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</untitled-ontology-3:referenciaRE>
        <untitled-ontology-3:sequencia rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#decimal">11</untitled-ontology-3:sequencia>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#CasoUso -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#CasoUso">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#Alpha"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:eProgredidoPor rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#AnalisarParteCasoUso"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:eProgredidoPor rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#DividirCasosUso"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:eProgredidoPor rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#EcontrarAtoreseUC"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:eProgredidoPor rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#InspecionarCasoUso"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:eProgredidoPor rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#PrepararParteCasoUso"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:possui rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#EstruturaHUCompreendida"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:possui rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#HUSimplesCumprida"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:possui rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#HUSuficientesCumpridas"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:possui rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#MetaEstabelecida"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:possui rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#TodasHUCumpridas"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:Icone>&lt;p&gt;Icone Alpha&lt;/p&gt;</untitled-ontology-3:Icone>
        <untitled-ontology-3:descricao>&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;Apresenta&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Um caso de uso &amp;eacute; independente e sempre deixa o sistema em um estado consistente.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;O conjunto de todos os casos de uso fornece todas as formas &amp;uacute;teis de usar o sistema.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Para entender um caso de uso, contamos hist&amp;oacute;rias.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;As hist&amp;oacute;rias abordam como atingir a meta com sucesso e como lidar com quaisquer problemas que ocorram no caminho. Eles nos ajudam a entender o caso de uso e implement&amp;aacute;-lo parte por parte.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Um caso de uso &amp;eacute;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Uma sequ&amp;ecirc;ncia de a&amp;ccedil;&amp;otilde;es que um sistema executa que produz um resultado observ&amp;aacute;vel de valor para um usu&amp;aacute;rio espec&amp;iacute;fico.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Aquele comportamento espec&amp;iacute;fico de um sistema que participa de uma colabora&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o com um usu&amp;aacute;rio para entregar algo de valor para esse usu&amp;aacute;rio.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;A menor unidade de atividade que fornece um resultado significativo ao usu&amp;aacute;rio.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;O contexto para um conjunto de requisitos relacionados.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1 style=&quot;text-align: start;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size: 2.375em;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</untitled-ontology-3:descricao>
        <untitled-ontology-3:nome>&lt;p&gt;Caso de Uso&lt;/p&gt;</untitled-ontology-3:nome>
        <untitled-ontology-3:sequencia rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#decimal">7</untitled-ontology-3:sequencia>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


    <!-- http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#CategorizacaoCusto -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#CategorizacaoCusto">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#PraticaDivida"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:eParteDe rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#Mensuracao"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:implementadaPor rdf:resource="http://www.semanticweb.org/vivid/ontologies/2023/2/untitled-ontology-3#EstimarTiposCustoManuseioDivida"/>
        <untitled-ontology-3:classificacaoPratica>Geral</untitled-ontology-3:classificacaoPratica>
        <untitled-ontology-3:descricao>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12px;&quot;&gt;Categoriza&amp;ccedil;&amp;atilde;o de custo permite estimar v&amp;aacute;rios tipos de custo de manuseio da d&amp;iacute;vida &amp;nbsp;incorrida.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</untitled-ontology-3:descricao>
